==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: President
<hw>Pres"i*dent</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Occupying the first rank or
chief place; having the highest authority; presiding.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His angels <qex>president</qex>⟦br⟧
In every province.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>President</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: President
<hw>Pres"i*dent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧sident</ets>, L. <ets>praesidens</ets>,
<ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>praesidere</ets>. See
<er>Preside</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who is elected or
appointed to preside; a presiding officer, as of a legislative
body.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The chief officer of a
corporation, company, institution, society, or the like.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The chief executive officer of the government in
certain republics; <as>as, the <ex>president</ex> of the United
States</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A protector; a guardian; a presiding genius.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Just Apollo, <qex>president</qex> of verse.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presidential</ent>⟦br⟧
